08/03/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Croatian Prime Minister Ivo Sanader expressed optimism Wednesday (March 7th) about opening all chapters of the acquis this year and completing EU accession talks in 2008. During a visit to the European Parliament (EP), Sanader met with Socialist deputies, saying much depends on the EU's timetable for amending its treaties, in order to create an institutional basis for admitting another member. On Thursday, he meets with EP President Hans-Gert Poettering and EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn. (Vjesnik - 08/03/07; HINA, HRT - 07/03/07)
